{{Not to be confused with|March 12}}<!--hatnote--> {{afc comment|1=This article as with the other date articles is relatively limited in scope to Japan. Reviewing the translation of this is good and also adding content translated from Chinese and Korean wikipedias will also be good. Both wikipedias are also relatively centered around their own countries for their Lunisolar calendar dates[[User:Immanuelle|Immanuelle]] ([[User talk:Immanuelle|talk]]) 00:16, 28 April 2025 (UTC)}} {{Globalize|article|Japan|date=April 2025}} {{Expand Chinese|1=三月十二|topic=hist|date=April 2025}} {{Expand Korean|1=음력 3월 12일|topic=hist|date=April 2025}} {{Lunisolar March|qq=}} '''March 12''' is the 12th day of the month {{ill|March (Lunisolar)|ja|3月 (旧暦)|lt=March (Yayoi)|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/March (Lunisolar)|qq=}}, the 3rd month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=}}. Its {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Rokuyō|qq=}} day is {{ill|Tomobiki|ja|友引|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tomobiki|qq=}}.
== Events == * [[:en:Ansei|Ansei]] 5th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1858]] [[:en:April 25|April 25]]) – In the event known as {{ill|Teimin Hachijukkyo Ressan Jiken|ja|廷臣八十八卿列参事件|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Teimin Hachijukkyo Ressan Jiken|qq=}}, officials such as [[:en:Iwakura Tomomi|Iwakurakura Toshimi]] and others from the pro-【攘夷】 court, numbering 88 non-aristocratic courtiers, staged a sit-in to oppose the signing of the {{ill|Treaty of Amity and Commerce|ja|修好通商条約|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Treaty of Amity and Commerce|qq=}}. * [[:en:Bunkyū|Bunkyū]] 3rd year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1863]] [[:en:April 29|April 29]]) – The [[:en:Shinsengumi|Shinsengumi]] became custodians of the [[:en:Aizu Domain|Aizu Domain]] and began referring to themselves as the {{ill|Mibu Rōshi-gumi|ja|壬生浪士組|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Mibu Rōshi-gumi|qq=}}.
== Births == * [[:en:Kan'ei|Kan'ei]] 10th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1633]] [[:en:April 20|April 20]]) – [[:en:Emperor Go-Kōmyō|Gōkōmei Tennō]], the 110th [[:en:Emperor of Japan|Emperor of Japan]] (died [[1654]]). * [[:en:Hōei|Hōei]] 5th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1708]] [[:en:May 2|May 2]]) – {{ill|Yuasachōzan|ja|湯浅常山|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yuasachōzan|qq=}}, a Confucian scholar ({{ill|Ru|ja|儒学者|zh|儒生|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ru|qq=}}) (died [[1781]]).
== Deaths == * [[:en:Hōei|Hōei]] 2nd year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1705]] [[:en:April 5|April 5]]) – [[:en:Itō Jinsai|Itō Jinsai]], a Confucian scholar ({{ill|Ru|ja|儒学者|zh|儒生|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ru|qq=}}) (born [[1627]]). * [[:en:Bunkyū|Bunka]] 3rd year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1806]] [[:en:April 30|April 30]]) – [[:en:Onogawa Kisaburō|Onogawa Kisaburō]], a 5th-generation {{ill|Yokozuna|ja|横綱|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yokozuna|qq=}} (born [[1758]]).
